    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Remembering Sealy</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By CHRIS BROUSSARD</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Broussard, Chris</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Number of Indiana Pacers players flew to New York on private jet after playoff game against New York Knickerbockers for Malik Sealy's funeral; rest of team flew in later for late afternoon practice (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mark Jackson, Reggie Miller, Al Harrington, Dale Davis and Chris Mullin flew to New York on a private jet after Thursday's game to attend the funeral for Malik Sealy this morning in Manhattan. The rest of the team flew in this morning for a late afternoon practice.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Mark Jackson, Reggie Miller, Al Harrington, Dale Davis and Chris Mullin flew to New York on a private jet after Thursday's game to attend the funeral for Malik Sealy this morning in Manhattan. The rest of the team flew in this morning for a late afternoon practice.</p>
        <p>''It was very tough, but at the same time, it was one in which we celebrated his life and the way he lived it and the impact he made,'' Jackson said. ''There were a lot of tears but also a lot of celebrating. My prayers continue to go out to the family.''</p>
        <p>CHRIS BROUSSARD</p>
        <p>PRO BASKETBALL: NOTEBOOK</p>
      </block>
